article_text: Will Sherard, one of Milwaukee’s most notorious landlords, has routinely paid the minimum on fines for hundreds of building code violations, even as he buys new properties. That game may be ending.

og.description: A key measure of household recycling in Wisconsin shows a drop since 2011 when Gov. Scott Walker's administration sharply cut state subsidies to communities. Are Walker and the GOP-controlled Legislature to blame for people recycling less?
